      • filter

        public ProteinFastaFileDataStoreBuilder filter(Predicate<String> filter)
        Only include the FastaRecords which pass the given Predicate for the ID. If a filter is not given to this builder, then all records in the fasta file will be included in the built FastaDataStore.

        If both this method and AbstractFastaFileDataStoreBuilder.filter(Predicate) are used, then the ID filter is applied first and then any remaining records are filtered with this filter.

        If this method is called multiple times, then the previous filters are overwritten and only the last filter is used.

        Overrides:
        filter in class AbstractFastaFileDataStoreBuilder<AminoAcid,ProteinSequence,ProteinFastaRecord,ProteinSequenceDataStore,ProteinFastaFileDataStore>
        Parameters:
        filter - a Predicate instance that can be used to filter out specified fasta records BY ID; can not be null.
        Returns:
        this.
        See Also:
        #filterRecord(Predicate)

      • hint

        public ProteinFastaFileDataStoreBuilder hint(DataStoreProviderHint hint)
        Provide a DataStoreProviderHint to this builder to let it know the implementation preferences of the client. If no hint is given, then this builder will try to store all the fasta records in memory which may cause an Exception if there isn't enough memory. The DataStoreProviderHint is just a guideline and may be ignored by this builder when determining which FastaDataStore implementation to chose to build in AbstractFastaFileDataStoreBuilder.build().
        Overrides:
        hint in class AbstractFastaFileDataStoreBuilder<AminoAcid,ProteinSequence,ProteinFastaRecord,ProteinSequenceDataStore,ProteinFastaFileDataStore>
        Parameters:
        hint - an instance of DataStoreProviderHint; can not be null.
        Returns:
        this
        See Also:
        DataStoreProviderHint

      • filterRecords

        public ProteinFastaFileDataStoreBuilder filterRecords(Predicate<ProteinFastaRecord> filter)
        Description copied from class: AbstractFastaFileDataStoreBuilder
        Only include the FastaRecords which pass the given Predicate. If no predicates are given to this builder, then all records in the fasta file will be included in the built FastaDataStore.

        If both this method and AbstractFastaFileDataStoreBuilder.filter(Predicate) to filter by ID are used, then the ID filter is applied first and then any remaining records are filtered with this filter.

        If this method is called multiple times, then the previous filters are overwritten and only the last filter is used.

        Overrides:

        Returns:

        See Also:

      • build

        public ProteinFastaFileDataStore build()
                                throws IOException
        Parse the given fasta file and return a new instance of a FastaDataStore using all the input parameters given so far. If not all optional parameters are set then default values will be used:
        • If no DataStoreFilter has been specified by #filter(DataStoreFilter), then all FastaRecords will be included in this FastaDataStore.
        • If no DataStoreProviderHint has been specified by AbstractFastaFileDataStoreBuilder.hint(DataStoreProviderHint), then this builder will try to store all the FastaRecords that meet the DataStoreFilter requirements in memory. This may cause out of memory errors if there is not enough memory available.
        Overrides:
        build in class AbstractFastaFileDataStoreBuilder<AminoAcid,ProteinSequence,ProteinFastaRecord,ProteinSequenceDataStore,ProteinFastaFileDataStore>
        Returns:
        a new FastaDataStore instance; never null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem parsing the fasta file.
        See Also:
        AbstractFastaFileDataStoreBuilder.hint(DataStoreProviderHint)
